Rails 2.1: Named Scope | RailsRocket
Rails 2.1 introduces something called named scopes; named scopes allow you to create named collections on a class-level for your models, such as Article.published. You can chain named scopes together, and even create parameterizable scopes by using the lambda keyword; you can pass in variables, of a sort, and Rails will plug the values into your named scope queries.
